c3506bd1-f8d4-45cd-aba9-de497dc98ff4.3024f8a0-29ff-49c3-996b-4e5d69b59c36.description=
Computes a mathematical operation.

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the first value
value2 - the second value
operator - operation to perform (+,-,*,/,%);

Responses\:
success - the expression was evaluated.
failure - the expression could not be evaluated.

Returns\: the value of the expression.
c3506bd1-f8d4-45cd-aba9-de497dc98ff4.5d02b8c6-58b4-4016-9d67-730adce080c9.description=Iterates through a list of values.If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. c3506bd1-f8d4-45cd-aba9-de497dc98ff4.62346151-f19b-4302-892c-2ec3e2ffe047.description=

If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. c3506bd1-f8d4-45cd-aba9-de497dc98ff4.description=
Calculates the average usage across all disks in a host.
WMI query does not work in Windows 2000, Windows NT 4.0, and Windows Me/98/95.

Inputs\:
host - the host to measure disk usage on.
username - username for host.
password - password for username.

Responses\:
success - the operation completed.
failure - something went wrong.

Returns\:
the average disk usage.
